@startuml
' @id(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
' Current-side use-case view of the `mdd view` interactive diagram viewer.
' Scope: the "writing in the UI" behavior — painting rendered model
' diagrams (shapes + text) onto the screen. Text now renders.
title mdd view — diagram viewer (current)

left to right direction

actor "Developer" as Dev

rectangle "mdd-viewer" {
  usecase "View rendered diagram\n(shapes AND text legible)" as View
  usecase "Browse model files" as Browse
  usecase "Pan and zoom canvas" as PanZoom
  usecase "Inspect trace graph" as Graph
  usecase "Inspect model IDs and trace links" as Trace
}

Dev --> View
Dev --> Browse
Dev --> PanZoom
Dev --> Graph
Dev --> Trace

View ..> Browse : <<include>>
View ..> PanZoom : <<extend>>
Graph ..> Trace : <<include>>

note right of Browse
  Today: a single flat, alphabetical scroll
  list of every model file (left rail). No
  directory tree, no cycle grouping, and no
  before/after diff view exist in the code.
end note

note bottom of Trace
  Right "MODEL CONTEXT" panel today: file path,
  kind, a raw @id list, and mechanical trace
  links (from → relation → to) plus test paths
  for the selected id. There is NO human-readable
  description of the action / cycle that created
  a diagram element, and no per-element annotation
  surfaced on clicking an element.
end note

note bottom of View
  Reads pre-rendered SVGs from .mdd/rendered/.
  If no models are mapped/rendered the canvas
  shows "No rendered output". Text rendering is
  realized by SEQ-RENDER-DIAGRAM-PAGE, which
  consults a populated font database
  (DOM-FONT-DATABASE) before rasterizing.
end note
@enduml
